# Git Workflow

## Standard Flow

```
Local development → commit → push to main → User pulls in Codespaces → Test in Codespaces
```

1. Make changes locally
2. `git add . && git commit -m "[description]"` 
3. `git push origin main`  ← Agent does this every time
4. User runs `git pull origin main` in Codespaces
5. GitHub = source of truth for all environments

**Agent MUST commit AND push after every session. Never leave push for the user.**

## Safe Pull Procedure

Always check status before pulling:

```bash
git status
```

| State | Action |
|-------|--------|
| Uncommitted changes exist | Commit or stash first, then pull |
| Local commits not pushed | Push first, then pull |
| Clean and up to date | Safe to pull |
| Ahead of origin | Push first |

